author: Gary Drapcho
title: Gannon's Nadler breaks D2 Record
text:
Gannon's Nadler breaks D2 Record Posted:   
Gannon University announced today that Knights senior QB Liam Nadler has broken the NCAA Division II record for consecutive passes without throwing an interception. His streak of 308 passes spans nine games going back to October 4th, 2014 at Slippery Rock. Nadler already has etched his name in the Gannon record books with career records in passing yards and touchdown passes and could become the all-time total offense leader before the end of the season. Gannon hosts Slippery Rock at noon on Saturday. Current Conditions
